# Architecture Constraints

## API surface

- ONE router per domain resource — no duplicate `restaurants` + `restaurants_enhanced` pattern for new work
- Deprecate `enquiries_standalone` — use `/restaurants/{restaurant_id}/enquiries` only
- Prefix all tenant resources: `/restaurants/{restaurant_id}/{resource}`

## Data layer

- Beanie `Document` for persistence; separate `Create`/`Update`/`Response` Pydantic models
- String IDs in API responses; ObjectId internal only
- Add indexes when adding new list/filter queries

## Frontend

- Types must match backend — prefer OpenAPI codegen over manual duplication
- API calls through `apiClient` singleton — no raw fetch scattered in components
- Restaurant context required for all dashboard data fetching

## Background work

- Email polling NOT in API process for new features — use worker entry point
- Long-running tasks: job queue pattern, not blocking HTTP handler

## AI integration

- Cap input size to LLM endpoints
- Return typed extraction responses, not raw dict
- Log provider name and prompt version, not full customer PII

## Error handling

- Production 500 responses: generic message only
- Log full exception server-side with request ID

## Before merging structural changes

Read affected audit dimension in `teardown-sample/00_AUDIT/` and confirm finding is addressed or explicitly deferred in task.
